    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 represents the pinnacle of analog performance. Under the hood, the S54B32 straight-six remains the centerpiece, featuring a high-pressure Double VANOS system and individual throttle bodies that provide instantaneous throttle response up to an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered through a precise 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox to the rear wheels via an M Variable Differential Lock. This example boasts a reinforced rear subframe and has undergone a comprehensive rod bearing service, ensuring mechanical longevity. The suspension geometry remains taut, with zero bushing deflection, and the factory Alpine White paint retains a deep luster with no evidence of panel gap misalignment. A truly concours-ready specimen for the discerning purist.",
